at riparian corridors may play as dispersal enhancers in unsuitable habitats and limitations concerning the modelling techniques used here, may have also contributed for the observed results. Refining the methodology employed here in the future, by accounting spatial and temporal scales that likely describe more realistically how processes responsible for genetic connectivity operate, is fundamental to obtain more robust results. This is very important, if conservation authorities want to reduce the effects of fragmentation in Mediterranean species in a near future..
